      • dropNA

        public DDF dropNA(IHandleMissingData.Axis axis,
         IHandleMissingData.NAChecking how,
         long thresh,
         List<String> columns)
           throws DDFException
        This function filters out rows or columns that contain NA values, Default: axis=0, how='any', thresh=0, columns=null, inplace=false
        Specified by:
        dropNA in interface IHandleMissingData
        Parameters:
        axis - = 0: drop by row, 1: drop by column, default 0
        how - = 'any' or 'all', default 'any'
        thresh - = required number of non-NA values to skip, default 0
        columns - = only consider NA dropping on the given columns, set to null for all columns of the DDF, default null
        Returns:
        a DDF with NAs filtered
        Throws:
        DDFException

      • fillNA

        public DDF fillNA(String value,
         IHandleMissingData.FillMethod method,
         long limit,
         AggregateTypes.AggregateFunction function,
         Map<String,String> columnsToValues,
         List<String> columns)
           throws DDFException
        This function fills NA with given values. Default using a scalar value fillNA(value,null, 0, null, null, null, false)
        Specified by:
        fillNA in interface IHandleMissingData
        Parameters:
        value - a scalar value to fill all NAs
        method - = 'ffill' for forward fill or 'bfill' for backward fill
        limit - = maximum size gap for forward or backward fill
        function - aggregate function to generate the filled value for a column
        columnsToValues - = a map to provide different values to fill for different columns
        columns - = only consider NA filling on the given columns, set to null for all columns of the DDF
        inplace - = false: result in new DDF, true: update on the same DDF
        Returns:
        a DDF with NAs filled
        Throws:
        DDFException
